"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vsb1665702989292.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vsb1665702989292.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vsb1665702989292.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vsb1665702989292\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Initiating Printing\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__initiating_printing_194086\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You initiate the print process from within Uniface using the Proc <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> command or the ^Print structure editor function.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64718e1_d64719e1_d64720e1\">Unless explicitly specified, either in parameters to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> command or in the Print dialog displayed by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print/read</span>, Uniface uses the following default values for the print mode and print job model:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__li_d28106e1_d28107e1_d28108e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print mode:</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">All</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__li_d28109e1_d28110e1_d28111e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print job model:</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">PRINTER</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__fig_d64721e1_d64722e1_d64723e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Uniface Print Dialog</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Uniface Print dialog\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/printdialog.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__topic_d42797e1_d42798e1_d42799e1_d42800e1_d42801e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d150303e94\">\n                 \n print and print/ask\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64730e1_d64731e1_d64732e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> statement can be used anywhere in a form or report to start printing. It is executed unseen by the user and is therefore best used in reports.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64733e1_d64734e1_d64735e1\">In forms, you can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print/ask</span> to prompt for information, enabling the user to choose a different printer or a different layout to suit their requirements. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print/ask</span> statement takes the supplied parameters (print job model and print mode) and presents the user with the Print form already filled in. This allows users to interactively tailor the printer specifications according to their requirements.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64736e1_d64737e1_d64738e1\">On Windows platforms, it is also possible to use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print/preview</span> to display the Print Preview window.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__topic_d42802e1_d42803e1_d42804e1_d42805e1_d42806e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d150303e122\">\n                 \n ^PRINT and the Print Trigger\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64742e1_d64743e1_d64744e1\">The print trigger is a component-level trigger that is activated by the ^PRINT Structure Editor function (usually mapped to a Print key). This trigger lets you control any print process initiated by the user. You can write ProcScript in this trigger which tests for certain conditions (such as the user's privileges), or, for example, run a password form component before allowing the print to continue.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vsb1665702989292__p_d64745e1_d64746e1_d64747e1\">If the print trigger is empty (which it is by default), Uniface implicitly executes <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print/ask</span>, displaying the Print dialog with the default values for the print job model and print mode.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533149\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533149\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Initiating Printing Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Initiating Printing You initiate the print process from within Uniface using the Proc print command or the ^Print structure editor function. Unless explicitly specified, either in parameters to the print command or in the Print dialog displayed by print/read , Uniface uses the following default values for the print mode and print job model: Print mode: All Print job model: PRINTER Figure 1. Uniface Print Dialog print and print/ask The print statement can be used anywhere in a form or report to start printing. It is executed unseen by the user and is therefore best used in reports. In forms, you can use print/ask to prompt for information, enabling the user to choose a different printer or a different layout to suit their requirements. The print/ask statement takes the supplied parameters (print job model and print mode) and presents the user with the Print form already filled in. This allows users to interactively tailor the printer specifications according to their requirements. On Windows platforms, it is also possible to use print/preview to display the Print Preview window. ^PRINT and the Print Trigger The print trigger is a component-level trigger that is activated by the ^PRINT Structure Editor function (usually mapped to a Print key). This trigger lets you control any print process initiated by the user. You can write ProcScript in this trigger which tests for certain conditions (such as the user's privileges), or, for example, run a password form component before allowing the print to continue. If the print trigger is empty (which it is by default), Uniface implicitly executes print/ask , displaying the Print dialog with the default values for the print job model and print mode. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}